body:
Is it required to completely remove this functionality? The index of the Original quality stream seems to be exposed as `OriginalFileIndex` and we can check if PikPak have presented the option for Original quality stream to the user using `Medias[].IsVisible`

So one way to remedy this might be to change https://github.com/rclone/rclone/blob/243bcc9d0787276ccaccbbd914d70ede6a0305e6/backend/pikpak/pikpak.go#L1445-L1448

to something like

```go
	if len(info.Medias) > 0 && info.Medias[info.OriginalFileIndex].Link != nil && info.Medias[info.OriginalFileIndex].IsVisible {
		fs.Debugf(o, "Using a media link")
		o.link = info.Medias[info.OriginalFileIndex].Link
	}
```
or check the MediaName property:
```go
	if len(info.Medias) > 0 {
		for _, media := range info.Medias {
			if media.MediaName == "Original" && media.Link != nil && media.IsVisible {
				fs.Debugf(o, "Using a media link")
				o.link = media.Link
			}
		}
	}
```
